          <p><strong>You want articles published:</strong> theStacc ($99/mo). <strong>You write but want NLP scoring:</strong> Surfer SEO ($89/mo). <strong>You want brand voice control:</strong> Jasper ($49/mo). <strong>Cheapest credible generator:</strong> Koala.sh ($9/mo).</p>
        </div>

        <div class="inline-cta">
          <div class="cta-copy">
            <h4>Want generated content that publishes itself?</h4>
            <p>theStacc generates, optimises, and publishes SEO articles end-to-end. <strong>$99/mo content SEO</strong> — articles live on your CMS without an editor to open.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="cta-action">
            <a href="/demo/" class="cta-btn-inline">See a live demo <span>→</span></a>
            <span class="cta-meta">No card · 15-min walkthrough</span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <h2 id="what-is">The 3 layers of SEO content generation</h2>
        <p>Every "SEO content generation tool" lives in one of three layers. Map your need to the layer before reading reviews:</p>

        <ol>
          <li><strong>Generation-first</strong> — Jasper, Koala.sh, Scalenut. Write the article from a prompt or brief.</li>
          <li><strong>Optimisation-first</strong> — Surfer, NeuronWriter, Outranking. Score and tune what you wrote against the SERP.</li>
          <li><strong>End-to-end platforms</strong> — theStacc, Frase. Research → generate → optimise → publish.</li>
        </ol>

        <div class="callout callout-warn">
          <div class="callout-label">The generator-only trap</div>
          <p>Generation without optimisation produces articles that read fine and rank nowhere. Optimisation without generation slows down a human writer. The win in 2026 is owning the full loop — either by stacking tools manually or buying a platform that already did it.</p>
        </div>

        <h2 id="how-we-tested">How we tested all 10 tools</h2>
        <p>Same briefs, same sites, same 90-day window.</p>

